The paper discusses the integration of sensor technologies, mobile devices, and wearables through the Web of Things (WoT), which involves leveraging Web standards for interoperability. This suggests a focus on distributed computing (cs.DC) and software engineering (cs.SE) for developing the Smart Web Services (SmartWS) framework. Additionally, the paper mentions context-based adaptation and cognition, which could relate to computational engineering (cs.CE) and cybernetics (cs.CY). Finally, the paper presents a specific use case in the medical domain, which could involve human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
